Use the standard library
This is how to encode of message:
   Remember that result is message
   Remember that n is message's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in message
      When c is 65, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 116
      End when
      When c is 69, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 103
      End when
      When c is 73, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 107
      End when
      When c is 79, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 112
      End when
      When c is 85, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 118
      End when
      When c is 97, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 84
      End when
      When c is 101, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 71
      End when
      When c is 105, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 75
      End when
      When c is 111, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 80
      End when
      When c is 117, then:
         Remember that item i in result is 86
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> encode of [116, 101, 115, 116]
[84, 71, 83, 84]
>>> encode of [84, 104, 105, 115, 32, 105, 115, 32, 97, 32, 109, 101, 115, 115, 97, 103, 101]
[116, 72, 75, 83, 32, 75, 83, 32, 67, 32, 77, 71, 83, 83, 67, 71, 71]
>>> encode of "TEST"
"tgst"